# CODEOWNERS — auto-route PRs to the right reviewer(s).
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS file — when a PR touches matching paths, the listed
# owners are auto-requested as reviewers. Combined with branch-protection
# rules requiring 1+ approval, this is the auto-merge path.
#
# V107-CI: this file is the routing layer for the agent team. Each owner
# is a `mavis` global agent (see ~/.mavis/agents/<name>/agent.md). The
# agents can also be invoked manually via `mavis team plan run`.
#
# NOTE: GitHub CODEOWNERS expects GitHub usernames or team slugs, not
# Mavis agent names. The values below are documented for human +
# agent routing — to wire them into GitHub's reviewer system, add
# the corresponding GitHub user or team as a CODEOWNER via the
# org's team-mapping (e.g. map `mavis/coder` to a GitHub bot account
# that the agent's CLI auths as).
#
# Until that wiring exists, this file serves as a routing table that
# agents consult when the orchestrator delegates a review.

# ─── Default reviewer ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every PR gets at least the verifier (adversarial) and code-reviewer
# (line-by-line) look. The orchestrator auto-approves if both pass.
*  @mavis/verifier @mavis/code-reviewer

# ─── Domain routing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tests + CI workflow changes → qa + devops-automator pair
/.github/  @mavis/qa @mavis/devops-automator
/tests/  @mavis/qa
/vitest.config.ts  @mavis/qa

# Tauri shell, Cargo.toml, tauri.conf.json → tauri desktop specialist
/src-tauri/  @mavis/tauri-desktop-expert
/scripts/release.sh  @mavis/devops-automator

# Post-lifecycle state machine (the v0.9.41 fix lives here) → specialist
/lib/post-lifecycle/  @mavis/post-lifecycle-expert @mavis/verifier
/lib/persistence/  @mavis/post-lifecycle-expert
/hooks/useReconciler.ts  @mavis/post-lifecycle-expert

